 risk with each of the eight (related to surrounding conditions or the health of the Earth) categories 
 through a six-point Likert scale ranking (0 = not important at all and 6 = very important). This rating was 
 completed for each of the three risk levels. The importance of reducing risk for each category was then 
 used to guess  the person who responded's WTP for a reduction 
 in risk j for each (related to surrounding conditions or the health of the Earth) category i by taking 
